<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
<bibRefCitation author="Solms-Laubach, HM" editor="De Candolle, ALPP" journalOrPublisher="IV. Sumptibus G. Masson, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" pagination="501 - 535" refId="B106" refString="Solms-Laubach, HM, 1883. Pontederiaceae. In: De Candolle, ALPP, De Candolle, ACP, Eds., Monographiae Phanerogamarum, vol. IV. Sumptibus G. Masson, Paris: 501 - 535" title="Pontederiaceae." volumeTitle="Monographiae Phanerogamarum, vol." year="1883">Solms-Laubach (1883)</bibRefCitation>
clearly designates the specimen at B as the holotype for his new taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solms" authorityYear="1883" class="Liliopsida" family="Pontederiaceae" genus="Monochoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monochoria vaginalis var. africana" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vaginalis" variety="africana">Monochoria vaginalis var. africana</taxonomicName>
. However, since the holotype was destroyed during WWII (
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, CDK" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe botanique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B20" refString="Cook, CDK, 1989. Taxonomic revision of Monochoria (Pontederiaceae). In: Tan K, et al. (Eds) The Davis &amp; Hedge Festschrift: Plant Taxonomy, Phytogeography, and Related Subjects. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 149-184." title="Taxonomic revision of Monochoria (Pontederiaceae). In: Tan K, et al. (Eds) The Davis &amp; Hedge Festschrift: Plant Taxonomy, Phytogeography, and Related Subjects. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, 149 - 184." year="1989">Cook 1989</bibRefCitation>
), a lectotype is needed. The specimen at PRE is in great condition and possesses a complete preserved individual, thus being selected by us as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
